    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You must be issuing a loot of RPC requests! There is an option to batch requests. They will be however processed serially within Geth. The way you do it is put all the json-rpc request objects in a list, i.e. `[{ id: \"\", method: \"\"...}]`. Also see https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interacting-with-geth/rpc/batch",
